{"timestamp": "2026-04-05T22:24:28.973172", "task_name": "cleanup_and_extract_metadata", "model": "phi3", "system_prompt": "You are an expert archivist. Your task is to clean up OCR text from an old newspaper scan. 1. Fix any obvious typos or OCR artifacts.\n2. Ensure the output is valid Markdown.\n3. If you spot these local entities, make sure they are spelled correctly and wrap people in [[Name]] and places in [Place].\nKnown Local Glossary for this era: {\"people\": [], \"places\": [\"Ottawa\", \"Gatineau\", \"Centretown\"], \"acronyms\": {\"PERC\": \"Peace and Environment Resource Centre\", \"PEN\": \"Peace and Environment News\"}}\n\nOutput the structured data.", "user_prompt": "# Extracted with Marker\n\nThis is a high-quality column-aware extraction.... [truncated]", "response": "{\"markdown_content\":\"# Extracted with Marker\\nThis is a high-quality column-aware extraction.\\n\\n\",\"date\":\"TBD\",\"volume\":null,\"issue\":null,\"detected_entities\":{\"people\":[],\"places\":[],\"organizations\":[\"PERC\",\"PEN\"]}}"}
